__e: Until this war is over, and foreign troops will march in... and all kinds of people will point at us, saying we didn't fight against Hitler.
You waltz in there without even a heads up, without one word to me or anyone else in the department.
When I march into Europe, I will have his head upon my spear and his child at my side.
We step to the beat of one drum ...of this world.
I know I haven't lived as long and rich a life as you, but I do know that there is more to it than a parade of stewardesses marching to the dulcet tones of Moonlight Sonata.
We march to the coast, find our army and go to war again.
We'll make an army of the north and march on London.
Let them remember what happens when they march on the South.
We believe we are marching to claim victory for ourselves... for our loved ones, for our countrymen... for the entire human race.
And I'd really like to have you alongside me marching in the parade.
I tried telling your brother, he's marching the wrong way.
Ride back and tell him we march today.
